[[Image:Germanium.jpg|thumb|A piece of germanium]]
'''Germanium''' is a [[chemical element]]. It has the chemical symbol ''Ge''. It has the [[atomic number]] 32. It was found by Clemens Winkler. It is a shiny, hard, silver-white [[metalloid]]. The chemistry of Germanium is quite like [[tin]]. Germanium forms a large number of [[Organometallic compound|organometallic]] [[chemical compound|compounds]]. It is an important [[semiconductor]] material used in [[transistor]]s.

