[[File:Hf-crystal bar.jpg|thumb|Hafnium Crystal Bar, mady by [[Crystal bar process]]]] '''Hafnium''' is a [[chemical element]]. It has the chemical symbol '''Hf'''. It has the [[atomic number]] 72. It is a [[metal]]. It is silver gray. In chemistry it is placed in a group of metal elements named the [[transition metal]]s. The chemistry of hafnium is similar to [[zirconium]].
Hafnium is found in zirconium [[mineral]]s.
Hafnium is used in [[tungsten]] [[alloy]]s in [[filament]]s and [[electrode]]s. It is also used as a [[neutron]] [[absorber]] in [[control rod]]s in [[nuclear power plant]]s.
== Other pages == * [[Periodic table]] * [[List of common elements]] {{Periodic Table}}
{{chem-stub}}
[[Category:Chemical elements]] [[Category:Metals]] [[Category:Transition metals]] {{Link GA|de}} {{Link GA|en}}
[[zh:铪]]

[[File:Ta,73.jpg|thumb|Tantalum in a glass tube]]
'''Tantalum''' is a [[chemical element]]. Tantalum was named '''tantalium'''. It has the chemical symbol '''Ta'''. It has the [[atomic number]] 73. It is a [[wikt:rare|rare]] [[metal]]. It is hard and blue-gray. In chemistry it is placed in a group of metal elements named the [[transition metal]]s.

Tantalum does not easily [[corrosion|corrode]]. It is found in the [[mineral]] [[tantalite]].

{{Periodic Table}}
{{chem-stub}}

