[[zh:钨]]

[[Image:Rhenium_single_crystal_bar_and_1cm3_cube.jpg|thumb|Rhenium]]
'''Rhenium''' is a [[chemical element]].  It has the chemical symbol '''Re'''.  It has the [[atomic number]] 75.  It is a [[wikt:rare|rare]] [[metal]].  It is silver white.  In chemistry it is placed in a group of metal elements named the [[transition metal]]s.  The chemistry of rhenium is similar to [[manganese]].  It was the last [[Nature|natural]] element to be discovered.

Rhenium made as a [[by-product]] of [[molybdenum]] refinement. 

Rhenium is used in some manganese [[alloy]]s.  Rhenium-molybdenum alloys are [[superconductor]]s.


